// Renderer
// Renders Mermaid diagram syntax to SVG (and thumbnail buffers) using a JSDOM-backed Mermaid instance.

dom-setup is imported first to ensure the JSDOM globals are in place before mermaid loads.
A thumbnail cache (up to 100 entries, LRU-evicted) avoids re-rendering unchanged diagrams.

FUNCTION fixNodeDimensions(svg) -> string
  Find flowchart node groups whose rect and foreignObject have zero or incorrect dimensions.
  For each, calculate width from text length (10px per char + 24px padding, minimum 60px) and fix height to 36px.
  Replace both the rect dimensions and the foreignObject dimensions in the SVG string.

---

FUNCTION fixEdgeLabels(svg) -> string
  Find edge label foreignObjects with width="0" height="0".
  For each, calculate width from label text length (8px per char + 12px padding) and set height to 20px.
  Add x/y centering offsets.

---

FUNCTION fixViewBox(svg) -> string
  Scan the SVG for all translate transforms, rect elements, and circle elements to derive bounding coordinates.
  IF valid bounds are found, recompute the viewBox with 20px padding on all sides and update the max-width style.

---

FUNCTION renderSVG(content, theme) -> string
  CALLS: fixNodeDimensions (renderer), fixEdgeLabels (renderer), fixViewBox (renderer)
  Initialize Mermaid with the given theme and startOnLoad=false.
  Render the diagram to SVG. Apply fixNodeDimensions, fixEdgeLabels, and fixViewBox to compensate for JSDOM limitations.
  Return the corrected SVG string.

---

FUNCTION generateThumbnail(id, content) -> Buffer
  CALLS: renderSVG (renderer)
  Return the cached buffer if the id is already cached.
  Otherwise render the diagram to SVG and wrap it in a Buffer.
  IF the cache has reached 100 entries, evict the oldest entry before caching.
  Return the buffer.

---

FUNCTION clearCache() -> void
  Empty the thumbnail cache.
